name: src/ESComplexProject.js
ESComplexProject
description: Provides a runtime to invoke ESComplexProject plugins for processing / metrics calculations of projects.

name: constructor
description: Initializes ESComplexProject.

params.name: pathModule
params.description:
Provides an object which matches the Node path module. In particular the following entries must be provided:

(string)    sep - Provides the platform-specific path segment separator: `/` on POSIX & `\` on Windows.

(function)  dirname - Returns the directory name of a path, similar to the Unix dirname command.

(function)  extname - Returns the extension of the path, from the last occurance of the . (period) character to
                      end of string in the last portion of the path.

(function)  relative - Returns the relative path from from to to.

(function)  resolve - Resolves a sequence of paths or path segments into an absolute path.
params.descriptionRaw:
Provides an object which matches the Node path module. In particular the following
                               entries must be provided:
```
(string)    sep - Provides the platform-specific path segment separator: `/` on POSIX & `\` on Windows.

(function)  dirname - Returns the directory name of a path, similar to the Unix dirname command.

(function)  extname - Returns the extension of the path, from the last occurance of the . (period) character to
                      end of string in the last portion of the path.

(function)  relative - Returns the relative path from from to to.

(function)  resolve - Resolves a sequence of paths or path segments into an absolute path.
```

params.name: options
params.description:
module and project options including user plugins to load including:

(object)             module - Provides an object hash of the following options for the module runtime:
   (boolean)         loadDefaultPlugins - When false ESComplexModule will not load any default plugins.
   (Array<Object>)   plugins - A list of ESComplexModule plugins that have already been instantiated.

(object)             project - Provides an object hash of the following options for the project runtime:
   (boolean)         loadDefaultPlugins - When false ESComplexProject will not load any default plugins.
   (Array<Object>)   plugins - A list of ESComplexProject plugins that have already been instantiated.
params.descriptionRaw:
module and project options including user plugins to load including:
```
(object)             module - Provides an object hash of the following options for the module runtime:
   (boolean)         loadDefaultPlugins - When false ESComplexModule will not load any default plugins.
   (Array<Object>)   plugins - A list of ESComplexModule plugins that have already been instantiated.

(object)             project - Provides an object hash of the following options for the project runtime:
   (boolean)         loadDefaultPlugins - When false ESComplexProject will not load any default plugins.
   (Array<Object>)   plugins - A list of ESComplexProject plugins that have already been instantiated.
```

name: _pathModule
description: Stores a module which matches the NodeJS path module API.
descriptionRaw: Stores a module which matches the NodeJS path module API.

name: _plugins
description: Provides dispatch methods to all module plugins.
descriptionRaw: Provides dispatch methods to all module plugins.

name: _escomplexModule
description: Stores the ESComplexModule instance used for generating module reports.
descriptionRaw: Stores the ESComplexModule instance used for generating module reports.

name: analyze
description: Processes the given modules and calculates project metrics via plugins.

params.name: modules
params.description: Array of object hashes containing ast and srcPath entries. Optionally srcPathAlias and filePath entries may also be provided.
params.descriptionRaw:
Array of object hashes containing `ast` and `srcPath` entries. Optionally
                                  `srcPathAlias` and `filePath` entries may also be provided.

name: process
description: Processes an existing ProjectReport instance and calculates metrics via plugins.

params.name: projectReport
params.description: An instance of ProjectReport with a modules entry that is an Array of ModuleReports.
params.descriptionRaw:
An instance of ProjectReport with a `modules` entry that is an Array of
                                        ModuleReports.

name: analyzeAsync
description: Wraps in a Promise processing the given modules and calculates metrics via plugins.

name: processAsync
description: Wraps in a Promise processing of existing ProjectReport instance and calculates metrics via plugins.

Plugins

properly manage and or create initial data that are processed by the plugins.

name: onConfigure
description:
Initializes the default `settings` object hash and then invokes the `onConfigure` plugin callback for all loaded
plugins.

name: onProjectStart
description:
Initializes the default `report` object hash and then invokes the `onProjectStart` plugin callback for all loaded
plugins.

description:

report metrics.
